Package edu.cnm.deepdive.teamle.viewmodel

Class UserViewModel

java.lang.Object
androidx.lifecycle.ViewModel
edu.cnm.deepdive.teamle.viewmodel.UserViewModel
All Implemented Interfaces:
DefaultLifecycleObserver, LifecycleObserver
public class UserViewModel extends ViewModel implements DefaultLifecycleObserver
Provides access (for a UI controller or data-bound view) to the User entity instance corresponding to the current signed-in user, a user specified by its unique identifier (primary key value), and the full collection of users who have signed in to the app. This access includes persistence operations on individual User entity instances.

    • getUser

      public LiveData<User> getUser()
      Returns LiveData containing the User entity instance specified in the most recent invocation of setUserId(long). If there are any observers of the result returned by this method, the retrieval will be performed automatically on invocation of setUserId(long), and the observers will be invoked (asynchronously) with the result.

    • getUsers

      public LiveData<List<User>> getUsers()
      Returns the LiveData containing the full collection of User entity instances corresponding to all users who have signed in to the app (or at least, all users who have been signed in when this class has been instantiated).

    • save

      public void save(User user)
      Adds or updates (asynchronously) the User entity instance referenced by user in the app's persistent data store. If any of the LiveData instances returned by getCurrentUser(), getUser(), or getUsers() are being observed, the underlying retrievals will be re-executed (and the observers invoked) automatically as an asynchronous consequence of invoking this method.
      Parameters:
      user - Instance of the User entity class to be added to or updated in the persistent data store.
